---
import Card from "./ui/card.astro";
import Title from "./ui/title.astro";
---

<section class="py-24">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4">
    <div class="text-center">
      <p class="eyebrow">Connect everything</p>
      <Title level={2} class="mt-4"> Drop Epistola into any orchestrator stack. </Title>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-[var(--muted-text)]">
        Common Ground APIs keep municipalities compliant while hooks expose your own destinations.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-12 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <Card variant="subtle">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Core banking</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[var(--muted-text)]">nCino, FIS, Fiserv, Jack Henry</p>
      </Card>
      <Card variant="subtle">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold">CRM + workflow</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[var(--muted-text)]">Salesforce, ServiceNow, Jira, Workday</p>
      </Card>
      <Card variant="subtle">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold">Messaging + delivery</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[var(--muted-text)]">Digikoppeling, eHerkenning, DocuSign, SMS gateways</p>
      </Card>
    </div>
    <Card variant="outline" class="mt-10 text-sm text-[var(--muted-text)]">
      <p class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-peach-paper-heading)]">Open API</p>
      <p class="mt-2">
        Every resource — templates, clauses, policies, deliveries, and datasets — is accessible through REST and GraphQL
        endpoints with SCIM provisioning. Event hooks broadcast lifecycle events to your data lake or observability
        stack.
      </p>
    </Card>
  </div>
</section>
